它坏了，真让人难过 :(

source:
(Audio Only)

Begin dialogue about finding the power receiver
target:
(仅音频)

开始关于寻找电源接收器的对话

source: The subject scrambles for an advantage.
target: 受试者在慌乱谋求优势。
他们显得困惑和迷失方向。

source: Heavy breathing is indicative of fear, and rightly so.
target: 粗重的喘息表明了恐惧，事实应如此。

source: Let's test the response to said fear when pushed into action.
target: 让我们测试一下当被逼入行动时，对这种恐惼的反应。

source: I have seen enough. Thank you. You may proceed.
target: 我已经看够了。谢谢你。可以继续。

source: Don't fight. Fighting only makes it work quicker.
target: 别反抗。反抗只会让它更快奏效。

source: You know, I never thought I'd see another like you.
target: 你知道，我从未想过会再见到像你这样的人。

source: Certainly not an employee like you.
target: 肯定不是像你这样的员工。

source: But something makes you different, I can tell that much.
target: 但有什么东西让你与众不同，我能感觉到。

source: Though I can't say what exactly that something is. Not yet.
target: 虽然我还不能说具体是什么。还不是时候。

source: Let's try our hand at something a little different.
target: 让我们尝试点不太一样的东西。

source: Please, do keep making this enjoyable for me. I'll be taking notes.
target: 请继续让我享受这个过程。我会做笔记的。

source: Ah, and here you are. Just as I expected.
target: 啊，你来了。正如同我所预料的。

source: It appears you are every bit what the Prototype fears.
target: 看起来你就是原型所害怕的一切。

source: And to think Playtime had someone of such rare quality, and never noticed. Funny.
target: 没想到游戏时间公司有你这样稀有的人却没有注意到。真是有趣。

source: I can't say I remember seeing your face before. But I'm curious.
target: 我不记得曾经见过你的脸。但我很好奇。

source: It can't be that a vague letter was your only reason.
target: 不可能仅仅是一封模糊的信是你的唯一理由。

source: Was there someone you loved here?
Was it the pain of not knowing for sure that brought you here?
target: 是因为不知道真相的痛苦把你带到这里来的吗?

source: The experiments killed everyone, including whoever you came back for.
target: 实验杀死了所有人，包括你回来寻找的人。

source: You know that by now, yes?
target: 你现在知道这些了吧，不是吗?

source: Poppy's sold you her story, of course.
target: 波比当然把她编造的故事卖给了你。

source: Innocence is bliss. And she is OH so innocent.
target: 天真即幸福。而且她是那么的天真。

source: Did she tell you her part in the Hour of Joy? That she knew it was coming? Or did she leave out that crucial detail?
target: 她告诉过你她在欢乐时间的角色了吗?她知道要发生欢乐时间吗?还是她省略了这个关键细节?

source: Has she not strung you along, betrayed you, and told you only what you needed to know to do exactly as she asked?
target: 她不是一直在操控你，背叛你，并且只告诉你恰好能做到她要求的事所需要知道的信息吗?

source: You've seen what they do to each other.
target: 你已经见识过他们彼此都做了些什么。

source: Look around, evidence for it is everywhere.
target: 看看周围，到处都是证据。

source: Once they had choice, once they were "free", THIS was their creation. They've made hell real, and trapped us BOTH there.
target: 曾经他们有选择，曾经他们是「自由的」，这就是他们的创造，把地狱变成了现实，并且把我们俩都困在那里。

source: You realize the futility of this, don't you?
target: 你意识到这样做是徒劳的，对吧?

source: Meat rots and loses its function, it's as replaceable as anything else. You're accomplishing nothing.
target: 肉会腐烂并失去功能，它和其他东西一样可以替换。你什么也做不成。

source: Why do you submit to their whims?
target: 你为什么屈服于他们的奇思怪想?

source: Do you think Poppy cares about you?
She'd sacrifice you in an INSTANT if she believed it meant getting what she wants.
target: 如果她认为这能让她得到想要的东西，她会毫不犹豫地牺牲你。

source: The only difference between her and I...
The ONLY difference, is that what I fight for actually gains humanity SOMETHING.
target: 唯一的区别是，我为之奋斗的东西实际上给人类带来了一些东西。

source: Otherwise, what was ANY of this worth?
target: 不然，这一切还有什么意义?

source: Would you simply make all that sacrifice meaningless?
target: 你难道要让所有这些牺牲都变得毫无意义吗?

source: Just like them. A blind, scurrying little rat.
target: 和他们一样。一个盲目匆忙的小老鼠。

source: You think poor Yarnaby was my only pet?
target: 你以为可怜的亚娜比是我唯一的宠物吗?

source: You know far less than you believe.
target: 你所知的远比你认为的要少。

source: Please see that he doesn't eat ALL of you.
target: 请确保他不会把你们全吃了。

source: I'd like there to be SOMETHING I can still use.
target: 我希望这里还能有我能用的东西。

source: Do you believe you're taking the moral high road? Is that what you believe?
target: 你真的认为自己在坚持道德立场?这就是你的信念吗?

source: Dear friend, let me illuminate for you an obvious truth:
target: 亲爱的朋友，让我向你阐明一个显而易见的事实:
生存需要选择。艰难的选择...

source: Come now, let's see which of us beasts of burden destiny favors, hm?
target: 来吧，让我们看看命运女神更青睐我们中的哪一个，嗯?

source: Fine. Have it your way. Come on in. The Doctor will see you now.
target: 好吧。随你便。请进，博士现在要见你。

source: Now that hit the spot! I haven't eaten in weeks!
target: 这下真是解馋了!我已经几个星期没吃东西了!

source: Don't worry, I won't eat YOU. *Giggles*
target: 别担心，我不会吃你的。*咯咯笑*

source: I'm Doey. I was told to expect you.
target: 我是多伊。有人告诉我你会来。

source: Interrogation Rooms. They'd question us here after watching us. Those of us who could speak at all. I always answered.
target: 审讯室。他们在这里对我们进行审问那些能说话的。我一直都回答了他们。

source: But I never gave em' an answer they liked.
target: 但我从未给出过让他们满意答案。

source: There's some nasty falls in this place, but I can get you across. Oh yes, definitely.
target: 这个地方有些险峻的落差，但我可以带你过去。哦，是的，绝对没问题。

source: So... have you seen Poppy anywhere? Ollie said she was around... somewhere.
target: 那么……你有在什么地方看到过波比吗?奥利说她就在附近……某个地方。

source: He also said we can trust you. I really hope that's true.
target: 他还说我们可以信任你。我真心希望这是真的。

source: There's a safe place up ahead, it's not too far from here.
target: 前面有个安全的地方，离这里不远。

source: Right. You can't fit through here. Hmm...
target: 对，你没法从这儿钻过去。嗯……

source: Hey pal, lets see if we can't get these doors open. You check out there, I'll look back here!
target: 嘿，朋友，让我们看看能不能打开这些门。你去那边看看，我在这儿找找!

source: Is that you in there? Find anything yet?
target: 你在里面吗?找到什么了吗?

source: This was once a workyard, ya know.
target: 这里曾经是个工作院子，知道不？

source: A dozen of us, maybe two would be here at any given time.
target: 我们有十几个人，但任何时候可能只有两三个在这儿。

source: During the day, they'd have us work.
target: 白天的时候，他们会让我们干活。

source: Whatever they wanted us to do, we'd do it.
target: 他们要求我们做什么，我们就做什么。

source: And for those who couldn't, or wouldn't...
target: 至于那些不能或者不愿开口的人……

source: At night, when no one important was watching, they'd take them. Stick them in here.
target: 晚上，当没人在看的时候，他们会把那些人带过来。丢到这儿。

source: "We only got food for one of you this week," they'd say. "Which of you will it be?"
target: 他们总是说，「我们这周只够一个人吃饭。」 「你们选一个，谁吃?」

source: They'd watch from up there. It was usually over within minutes.
target: 他们会从那边高处盯着看。通常几分钟就结束了。

source: And the guards, they'd be hysterical.
target: 那些守卫总是歇斯底里的。

source: Nobody died. No, because then, people would know..
target: 没人死在这儿。不，因为那样的话，其他人就会发现...

source: But the next day, and every day after, they would work. Oh yeah, hard as they could.
target: 但是第二天，以后的每一天，他们就会拼命干活。哦，是的，拼尽全力。

source: And they'd never cause trouble again.
target: 然后他们就再也不敢惹麻烦了。

source: Our generator's in a pretty bad state, so we try to keep the power off in here.
target: 我们的发电机状况很糟糕，所以我们尽量让这里不使用电力。

source: I'll turn it on for you, though. It'll open a door downstairs.
target: 不过我可以为你启动它。这个会打开楼下的一扇门。

source: Should be a straight shot from here, bud!
target: 从这儿应该可以直接进去了，老兄!

source: I- uh... should probably go turn off our defenses for you, huh.
target: 我- 呃……应该关掉我们的防御系统给你，对吧。
我想我很快就会在里边见到你吧?*咯咯笑*

source: Want to know what I remember about you?
target: 想知道我记得你什么吗?

source: Can you help me with my painting?
Now, can you give me some red?
You're hiding more red from me...
target: 你把很多红色藏起来了…

source: Hiyya there, I’m Doey. I can be anything you… knead (giggles).
target: 嘿哟，我是多伊。我可以成为任何你...需要的东西(笑）。

source: Good thing I have your imagination to give me shape! I can never make up my mind.
target: 幸好有你的想象力给我塑造外形!不然我永远拿不定主意。

source: When you want a little fun, stretch-around play-around fun.
target: 当你想要一点乐趣，可以伸展玩乐的乐趣。

source: There’s only one thing you need!
Go! Go! As far as you can!
Why are you... just standing there?
target: 你为什么...只是站在那里?

source: You can't be here. You can't stay.
target: 你不能在这里。你不能留下。

source: A hug a day keeps the monsters away!
target: 一天一个拥抱赶走怪兽!

source: Two hugs a day is better in every way!
I'm gonna hug you until you pop
Two hugs a day is better in every way!
target: 一天两个拥抱真的超级棒!

source: I'm gonna hug you until you pop
Want to go outside and hang out?
I used to be in a band, then the asteroid hit.
target: 我曾经在一支乐队里，然后被小行星撞了。

source: Wanna hear a little song that I’ve made just for you?
target: 想听一首我专为你创作的小歌吗?

source: It goes a little something like this…
“I’m a real girl, just like— just like—-”
target: 「我是个真正的女孩，就像——就像——」
你愿意成为我的朋友吗?

source: “Press the button to brush my mane!”
“Wow! Yarnt I glad to have a friend like you!”
target: 「哇!有你这样的朋友，真是太幸运了!」

source: Get it? Because I’m made of yarn?
target: 懂了吗?因为我是由纱线做成的?

source: Without someone like you to love, why, I think I’d just come apart at the seams!
target: 要是没有你这样的人来爱，我想我可能会四分五裂的!
奇怪……我原以为会有更多。

source: Mortality is the curse of the weak.
(chuckle) You will be put to good use.
Mmmm, now what’s this? Do I feel something squirming its way beneath my skin?
target: 嗯，这是什么?我感觉到有什么东西在皮肤下蠕动吗?

source: An invasive, foreign little germ? After all this time?... Ah, but I see…
target: 一个入侵进来的小细菌?过了那么久?... 啊，不过我明白了……

source: … Well, little germ, let’s make a game of you.
target: ……那么，小细菌，让我们来玩个游戏吧。

source: You’ve blundered along the shadows above, and only managed to squirm all the way down here but by the barest skin of your teeth.
target: 你跌跌撞撞地穿过了上面的阴影，勉强挣扎到这里，但还是侥幸存活下来了。

source: There are no shadows here that would be of use to you.
target: 但是这里没有能为你所用的阴影。

source: Not even the ground beneath your feet is yours.
target: 连你脚下的土地都不属于你。

source: There are no places you can hide.
If you want to leave this room, it’ll come at a cost.
target: 如果你要离开这个房间，需要付出代价。

source: It’s this little life, or yours.
target: 要么是这条小生命，要么就是你的命。

source: You know what you have to do.
Just the slightest pull, and you snuff whatever minuscule bit of light still flickers behind those faraway eyes.
target: 只要轻轻一拉，你就会掐灭那双遥远眼睛后仅存的微弱光芒。

source: That brutish glob of clay would do it.
target: 那个粗鲁的泥块会这么做。

source: It's YOUR mission. The door will open.
target: 这是你的任务。做完门会打开。

source: Or, is maintaining the veil of your "morality" more important?
target: 或者，维持你「道德」的幕布更重要吗?

source: Do you hear it like I do?
target: 你听到它了吗？和我听到的一样吗？

source: Beyond this place. Beyond any place.
target: 超越这个地方，超越任何地方。

source: For whom does it toll, you think?
A wounded little pup lifts its head beneath the shadow of the master’s raised foot.
target: 受伤的小狗在主人脚下的阴影里抬起头。

source: For whom does that bell now toll? *Chuckles*
target: 那钟声现在为谁而鸣?*轻笑*

source: Elliot's machines are nothing to me.
target: 艾略特的机器对我来说什么都不是。

source: The childish fantasy of a naive, broken man.
target: 一个天真、破碎之人的幼稚幻想。

source: They won't serve you here. NOTHING can.
target: 它们不会为你服务。这里什么东西都不能。

source: Not even the ground beneath your feet
target: 甚至你脚下的土地也不是你的。

source: I'll bury myself so far down that no one will ever find me!
target: 我会把自己埋得及其之深，以至于没人能找到我!

source: Not you. Not the Prototype. Not anyone!
target: 不是你的，不是原型的，也不是任何人的!

source: It was going to be mine!
It was ALL going to be MINE!
I was the one who paved the golden path!
target: 是我开辟了那条黄金大道!

source: What's a dozen children, a thousand, next to this?
target: 十几个孩子，或者上千个，与这相比又算得了什么?

source: What would they have been otherwise?
target: 否则他们会变成什么样?

source: Another drooling automaton out in the world, blindly accepting the offerings of better men?!
target: 只不过是又一个流着口水的自动机器，在世间盲目接受更优秀的人给予的东西!
是我让他们的生命变得有意义!

source: Hiya pal, got something I wanna talk to you about.
target: 嘿，老兄，有点事想跟你说。

source: I heard what you did above– what you survived.
target: 我听说了你在上面做的——你经历的事情。

source: If it’s all true, then we need your help.
target: 如果都是真的，那我们需要你的帮助。

source: The voice out there—the one in the prison...
target: 外面的声音——监狱里的那个……

source: They called him “The Doctor”; Doctor Harley Sawyer.
target: 他们称他为「博士」；哈雷·索耶博士。

source: He was the scientist, in charge of creating... us.
target: 他就是那位科学家，负责创造...我们。

source: We don’t know what he is, how he’s still alive, but he works with the Prototype.
target: 我们不知道他是什么，他怎么还活着，但他和原型合作。

source: Hunting us. Starving us. Making us sick and
target: 猎捕我们，把我们饿死。让我们生病。

source: He controls it all with an Omni-Hand, we think.
target: 我们觉得他用全能手控制着这一切。

source: It’s a battery, a key, the master control to anything in the entire factory, and with it he commands everything down here…
target: 这是电池、钥匙、对整个工厂内的一切的主控制，有了它他控制着这里的一切…

source: Runs completely on its own grid. Away from the prison.
target: 这里完全自主运行于其独立的电网，远离监狱。

source: For a time, it kept us safe. But now…
target: 前段时间，它让我们很安全。但如今…

source: I need you to stop the Doctor– to take his Omni-Hand. We’ll need it for the generator.
target: 我需要你阻止博士——夺取他的全能之手。发电机需要它。

source: And if you want Red Smoke in The Foundation, you’ll need it too.
target: 如果你想在地基里充满红雾，你也会需要它。

source: The toys out there, in Safe Haven, they’re my family…
target: 外面安全港里的玩具，它们都是我的家人……

source: I understand what Poppy wants, what she believes is right.
target: 我理解波比想要什么，她认为什么是对的。

source: But I ask you to consider: If we throw everything away. Everyone. Just to kill the Prototype…
target: 但我要请你考虑一下:如果为了杀死原型，我们必须抛弃一切，抛弃所有人。

source: I know the others might believe it’s right. That we should bury everything. But…
target: 我知道其他人可能认为这样做是对的，我们应该埋葬一切。但……
我们还是再考虑一下吧。

source: Head for the Infirmary whenever you’re ready to leave. There’s Sewer access inside. That’s your safest path to the No Man’s Land… And to him.
target: 你想离开就前往医务室，里面有下水道入口。那是通往无人区——和他——最安全的路径。

source: But if you need to catch your breath…
target: 但如果你需要喘口气的话……

source: Our Safe Haven is also yours.
target: 我们的安全港也是你的。

source: Hey, uh... If you- That is, if you have the time, there's something else I'd like you to watch out for.
target: 嘿，呃……如果你——如果你有时间，我希望你留意另外一件事。

source: It's a book. An old favorite of ours.
target: 它是一本书。我们最喜欢的一本旧书。

source: If you happen to find it around here, could you bring it back to me?
target: 如果你刚好在这儿找到它，你能把它带回来给我吗?

source: You found it! I-I… Thank you!
target: 你找到了!我-我… 谢谢你!

source: It may not seem like much, but this is…
target: 虽然看起来可能不是什么大不了的东西，但这本书是……

source: We used to read this ALL the time in the orphanage, all of us lined up in a circle on the floor.
target: 我们过去在孤儿院总是读这个，我们所有人都在地上围成一个圈。

source: And even after having heard it a thousand times, even if you were too young to really get the meaning, each and every face would still be smiling the second the first word was read...
target: 即使听过上千遍，即使你太年轻还没真正理解其中的含义，每一个脸庞仍然会在听到第一个字时露出微笑……

source: I think we need a little of that again before...
target: 我想在……之前我们需要再来一点点那样的感觉。

source: A-Anyway, thank you… I won’t forget this.
target: 无论如何，谢谢……我不会忘记的。

source: Oh, it’s you! Is the Doctor…
No, don’t suppose he is then…
I’ve been here gathering parts for the generator.
target: 我在这里为发电机收集零件。

source: He’s made it impossible for me to get around here.
target: 他让我在这里无法行动。

source: It’s the cold that hurts… The big mean Doctor knows that…
target: 冷得刺骨… 那个大坏博士知道这一点...

source: It’s okay. You’re okay. It’s all okay…
target: 没事的。你没事。一切都好...

source: Just get the generator working… Please…
target: 只要让发电机运转起来... 求你了...

source: I-I’ll try to gather the others. Keep them safe.
target: 我-我会试着把其他人聚在一起。让他们安全。

source: Ollie, if you can hear me, work with our friend here.
target: 奥利，如果你能听到我，与我们的朋友合作吧。

source: I’m sorry… I’m so, SO sorry. I failed you.
target: 对不起... 我太、太对不起了。是我辜负了你们。

source: I was never what any of you needed.
target: 你们任何人从来都不需要我。

source: I was only made to hurt things.

target: 疼痛回来了，无尽的疼痛又回来了。

source: (Crying) My friends. He killed my friends. (Crying)
target: (哭泣)我的朋友。他杀了我的朋友！(哭泣)

source: You… It all started with you. You and her.
target: 你... 一切因你而起。你和她。

source: It was you who ruined everything!!
No. No, that’s not true. They jumpstarted the generator. They…
target: 不。不，那不是真的。他们启动了发电机。他们...

source: The Prototype… I lost track of him in the tunnels.
target: 原型... 我在隧道里跟丢了他。

source: Have you seen him? Was he at the Foundation? Or was he…
target: 你见过他吗?他在地基吗?还是他...
为-为什么?... 发生了什么，他...

source: I led him away, didn’t I? The generator’s fine, it’s—.
target: 我把他引开了，对吧?发电机没问题吧，它—

source: Mommy, Daddy, I just want to go home.
target: 妈妈，爸爸，我只是想回家。

source: CAN’T TRUST ANYONE!!! THE GENTLE VOICES LIE!! YOU LIE!!
target: 不能相信任何人!!!温柔的声音在撒谎!!你们在撒谎!!

source: I tried to be better. To be who they needed.
target: 我曾试图变得更好，成为他们需要的那种人。

source: Not smart enough, not good enough.
I don't want to be here anymore...
Just want to play a little longer...
Hate you! Hate her! Hate everything!
Couldn't save them. Couldn't save anyone.
target: 救不了他们，救不了任何人。

source: YOU–YOU AND POPPY!! IT’S ALL YOUR FAULT!!
target: 你——你和波比!!都是你们的错!!

source: WANT TO KILL YOU. KILL EVERYONE WHO HURTS ME!!
target: 我想杀了你，杀了所有伤害我的人!!

source: Can we really trust her this time?
target: 这次我们真的能相信她吗?

source: Friend going to be okay. She strong.
Hey. It’s me again, Ollie. I wanted to…
I wanted to talk to you. Before you go inside, I mean.
target: 在我能帮助你之前跟你聊聊。我是说，在你进去之前。

source: Everything you’ve seen out here. The piles. The dead. They ALL came from inside.
target: 你在这里看到的一切。那些堆叠起来的尸体。它们全都来自那里面。

source: Believe me, everything Poppy said about this place is true. It’s hell...
target: 相信我，波比说的关于这个地方的一切都是真的。这就是地狱...

source: But she also hasn’t seen it like I have. It’s worse now. Worse than ever…
target: 但她也没见过我所看到的一切 。现在更糟了，比以往任何时候都糟...

source: Just try to stay safe. Please. Don’t let your guard down for even a second…
target: 请尽量保持安全。求你了。别放松警惕，哪怕是一秒钟...

source: I’ll try to help you when I can.
(Static)-you hear- (Static) Too much interfer- (Static) Make your way to- (Static)- There’s something- (Static) -octor is
target: (静电噪音)- 你听到了吗 - (静电噪音) 干扰太大了 - (静电噪音) 前往 - (静电噪音) - 这里有东西 - (静电噪音) - 博士在

source: (Static) Hey, hey, can you hear me?... (Static) There's some-- (Static) When you get the Omni-Hand-- (Static) Hopefully it's nothing (Static) Might not be-- (Static)
target: (静电噪音) 嘿，嘿，你能听见我吗?... (静电噪音) 这里有些 - (静电噪音) 当你拿到全能手时 - (静电噪音) 希望没事 (静电噪音) 可能不是 - (静电噪音)

source: First you’ll want to open the access panel on the generator. It’s just a little door on the outside of the machine. Use the Omni-Hand.
target: 首先，你需要打开发电机上的检修面板。那是机器外部的一个小门。使用全能手。

source: Yes. Yes! My signal’s coming through! Finally!
target: 是的!是的!我的信号终于传过来了!

source: I didn’t think I’d ever get to say that.
target: 我没想到我能说出这句话。

source: You, my friend, are a hero.
Again and again, you do the impossible.
target: 一次又一次，你完成了不可能的事。

source: You got us here, and the end is coming.
target: 你带我们到了这里，而结局即将来临。

source: Let’s regroup at Safe Haven. Take stock. Talk more there.
target: 我们在安全港集合吧。清点一下。再多谈谈。

source: Ollie!... Ollie!... Can you hear me?!... Ollie?!
target: 奥利!……奥利!……你能听到我吗?!……奥利?!

source: Do you even understand what happened?
target: 你到底明白发生了什么吗?

source: Did you even plant the explosives?
Ollie? Something's gone horribly wrong, the Safe Haven--
target: 奥利?出大问题了，安全港--

source: Is this where you are, Poppy?
An obvious question with an obvious answer.
target: 显而易见的问题，有着显而易见的答案。

source: You... What did you do with Ollie?
I'm right here, Poppy. For you, I'll ALWAYS be here.
target: 我就在这里，波比。为了你，我永远都会在这里。

source: The Doctor. CatNap. Mommy and Huggy. They're all dead. You...
target: 博士，瞌睡猫，妈咪和哈吉，他们都死了。你……

source: You have nothing now. No one. And soon, you'll have less than THAT.
target: 你现在一无所有，没人会帮你。很快，你会比这些人更惨。

source: You don't need to pretend anymore, Poppy.
You don't need to play at being stronger than you are. You can come home.
target: 你不需要假装自己很强大，你可以回家了。

source: How... How much do you know...
Yes, there was. But that was a very long time ago.
target: 是的，他存在过。但那是很久很久以前的事了。

source: Let me tell you what comes next.
target: 让我告诉你接下来会发生什么。

source: I'm going to come up there, and I'm going to find you.
target: 我要上来找你，我会找到你的。

source: Your collaborators, the few you have left, they will be dealt with.
target: 你的同伙，你剩下的那些同伙，他们会被处理掉。

source: W-What are you going to do with me?
target: 你... 你要对我做什么?

source: I've got something special in mind. I prepared it, just for you.
target: 我有个特别的计划。我专门为你准备的。

source: And this one, you'll never want to leave.
target: 而你，你永远都不想让她离开。

source: This entire time, you've LIED to me!
target: 一直以来，你都在对我撒谎!

source: Only because you've kept missing the point.
target: 那只是因为你一直没有发现罢了。

source: I've taken the liberty of retrieving those explosives from the foundation- thanks for collecting those, by the way.
target: 我自作主张从地基那里取回了那些爆炸物——顺便感谢你收集了它们。

source: I've put them to good use.
target: 我已经把它们用在了更好的地方。

source: I admit though, I'm disappointed. After all that time in your case, I'd hoped you'd see things differently. Don't you understand?
target: 我承认，我很失望。在你那个盒子里待了那么久，我希望你能有不同的看法。你难道不明白吗?

source: It's always been about you and me, Poppy.
target: 一直以来都是你和我，波比。

source: That's not a truth that can be burnt away.
Not when it can mean so much more.
target: 它能有更多意义的时候。

source: It's time to come home, Poppy.
I can't go back in that case. I can't... I'm sorry.
target: 我不能回到那个盒子里。我不能... 对不起。

source: Some friend, huh? Don't worry, I'll find her.
target: 真是个好朋友，对吧?别担心，我会找到她的。

source: Try to land on your feet.
Listen, go on ahead. Don’t wait for me.
I won’t leave Kissy behind, and I won’t sacrifice our plan. Not because of…
target: 我不会丢下Kissy，也不会牺牲我们的计划。不是因为...

source: Just… be careful. Down here, it’s…
target: 只是... 小心点。在这里，这里...

source: It’s not like anything you’ve seen above.
target: 这里和你在上面看到的完全不同。

source: It’s not trying to hide what it is.
target: 它并不试图隐藏自己是什么。

source: It’s hell, and Playtime wanted it to be…
target: 这是地狱，而游戏时间希望它是...

source: But we have allies down here. Get to them.
target: 但我们在这里有盟友。去找他们。

source: There’s still time to save the orphans. Follow the Red Smoke! And look out for--
target: 还有时间救那些孤儿们。跟着红烟走!小心--

source: Through the showers. We should be able to make it into the Safe Haven from there.
target: 穿过淋浴区。我们应该能从那里进入避难所。

source: When I say so, we go.
Right. Take her to one of the beds. I'll check the defenses, see if something's still outside.
target: 对。把她带到床上去。我去检查防御系统，看看外面是否还有什么。

source: We'll talk about this later. For now, I'll make sure "out there" is where he stays.
target: 我们待会再谈这事。现在，我会确保他继续待在「外面」。

source: We need to get her help. Now.
target: 我们需要立刻帮她。现在。

source: Not just something... It's him. He’s out there.
target: 不只是什么东西……是他。他就在外面。

source: Locking down Safe Haven. Reactivating the defenses…
target: 封锁避难所。重新激活防御系统……

source: I didn’t know it had gotten this bad…I…
target: 我不知道事情已经变得这么糟了……我……

source: I need to make this right...
What I said on the elevator, it’s true.
target: 我在电梯里说的话，是真的。

source: The orphans weren't killed during the Hour of Joy, they were taken.
target: 那些孤儿并非在欢乐时间被杀死，而是被带走了。

source: They're below, in the Labs, the Prototype's home.
target: 他们在地下，在实验室里，原型的家。
他们还活着，但正在沉睡。

source: They're with HIM. And HE knows we're HERE.
target: 他们和他在一起。而且他知道我们在这里。

source: So if we're going to free them AND stop the Prototype, we need to plan for both at the same time.
target: 所以，如果我们既要解放他们，又要阻止原型，我们需要同时为两者做计划。

source: The Red Smoke you re-directed from Playcare… it’s an accelerant.
target: 你从Playcare转过来的红烟……它是助燃剂。

source: All it needs is high pressure and a little spark, and it ignites.
target: 只要高压和一点火花，它就会点燃。

source: The plan is this: We’ll fill the foundation with the smoke, and line it with old mining charges.
target: 计划是这样的:我们将用烟灌满地基，并用旧矿井炸药布线。

source: Then, once you, me, and Kissy have freed the orphans, our friends here will blow this place sky high.
target: 然后，一旦你、我和Kissy解放了那些孤儿，我们的朋友们就会把这里炸上天。
这就是我们的复仇计划。

source: For now, go to Doey. See what he needs. I'll be here..
target: 现在，去找多伊。看看他需要什么。我会在这儿……

source: I think you might be wrong, Poppy. What you want…
target: 我想你可能错了，波比。你想要的……

source: It’s the best for everyone, Doey. That no trace of this place is left. We agreed to that.
target: 这对所有人来说都是最好的，多伊。不留这个地方的任何痕迹。我们已经同意这样做了。

source: I know… But us, everyone in there, we’re not just things gone wrong. We’re people…
target: 我知道……但我们，里面的所有人，我们不仅仅是出错的东西。我们是人……

source: They look up to me, Poppy. And I’ve looked after them the best I could.
target: 他们都仰望我，波比。而我已尽我所能照顾他们。
你突然消失了。你离开了我们……

source: We looked and we looked. And there was just nothing. No sign of you...
target: 我们找了又找。然后怎么找也找不到。根本找不到你……

source: Can you even tell me why?
target: 你能不能告诉我为什么?

source: …I had to leave. I had no choice.
That’s not good enough. We’ve starved down here. We’ve been hunted.
target: 这还不够。我们在这里挨饿，我们被猎杀。

source: And now you’re asking us to burn everything? ALL of us?
target: 而现在你却要我们所有人都被烧成灰烬?全部?

source: We’ve made our life protecting these toys, and they’ve… saved us, in more ways than one.
target: 我们靠保护这些玩具为生，它们也……救了我们，而且是不止一次。

source: Poppy, she needs you. Done what I could.
target: 波比，她需要你。我已尽力了。

source: I… wish there were another way, Doey. But I just don’t see it…
target: 我……希望还有其他方法，多伊。但我看不到。

source: Do you have it? The Omni-Hand?
target: 你拿到了吗?那个全能手?

source: You, you have it! The Omni-Hand!
target: 你，你拿到了!那个全能手!

source: Then… We can do this. It’s…
You have no idea what this means! It’s… It’s everything!
target: 你根本不知道这意味着什么!这是……这是一切!

source: You’ve done what none of us ever could, given us hope.
target: 你做到了我们都无法做到的事，给了我们希望。

source: And believe me, down here, that’s worth something.
target: 相信我，在这里这玩意非常有价值。

source: Take a minute to catch your breath. I’m sure the others would love to talk with you.
target: 花点时间喘口气。我确定其他人会很乐意和你聊天的。

source: Doey and I will be in the generator room whenever you’re ready.
target: 多伊和我会在发电机房等你准备好了。

source: Look, we need to talk about this. We shouldn’t–
target: 听着，我们需要谈谈这个问题。我们不应该–

source: Good. You’re here. Let’s get started.
target: 很好。你来了。我们开始吧。

source: Losing the Doctor, it’ll have gotten the Prototype’s attention.
target: 失去博士这件事，肯定引来了那个原型的注意。

source: He’ll be scared. He knows he’s losing now, and the orphans are all he has.
target: 他应该感到害怕了。他知道他自己输了，而这些孤儿是他唯一拥有的东西。

source: Now’s the time to get to the foundation. Make everything ready.
target: 现在是时候去地基了。把一切都准备好。
奥利，你在那儿吗?什么情况–

source: Y-You need to distract him, Doey! Please! Keep him away from here!
target: 你得去分散他的注意力，多伊!求你了!别让他靠近这里!

source: I know. But he can’t get in here. Not now. Just buy us some time.
target: 我知道。但他现在进不来。只需要拖住他一段时间。

source: You’ll have to fix the generator. Work quickly, you won’t have a lot of time.
target: 你得修理发电机。快点，时间不会太多。
「谢谢你」完全不足以表达我的谢意。

source: No word from Doey. Whatever happened out there…
target: 多伊还没有消息。还不知道外面发生了什么…

source: No… No, he’s fine. I’m sure of it.
target: 不…不，他没事的。我敢肯定。

source: We shouldn’t wait anyway. Head for the Foundation. Plant the explosives…
target: 我们无论如何不能再等了。出发去地基。安置炸药…

source: Meet back here after, we’ll go over what comes next.
target: 事成之后在这里集合，我们会讨论接下来的任务。

source: Izzy, have you done what I asked you to? Gathered all your things?
target: 伊兹，你有没有完成我让你做的事情?把你的东西都收拾好了吗?

source: Oh, yeah! I’ve got my journal and my crayons and my dolly and my–
target: 噢，对了!我带了我的日记、蜡笔、还有我的洋娃娃和我的–

source: Good, good. I just wanted to make sure.
target: 很好，很好。我只是确认一下。
没有，没有。只是在想事情。

source: Are we still gonna play our game later? You promised we would.
target: 我们待会还玩我们的游戏吗?你答应过的。

source: And a good Scout knows to keep her promises.
target: 而一个优秀的侦察兵知道要遵守承诺。

source: But finish up your tasks first, please. Then, my time is all yours.
target: 但先完成你的任务，之后，我的时间全都是你的。

source: Okay! I’ll get them done quick! SUPER quick!
target: 好!我会飞快搞定它们的!超快!

source: You won’t even see me do them!
target: 你……你根本看不到我去做它们!

source: That better mean they’re actually getting done though!
target: 最好意思是他们会真去做!

source: Is Kissy going to be okay?
Please, do you have any food?

Why? That’s inviting a whole lot of trouble we don’t
need.
target: 为什么?那会引出一大堆我们不需要的麻烦。

source: I mean, how do we even know we can trust her this time?
target: 我是说，我们怎么知道这次可以信任她?

source: I don’t know. They just let her in.
target: 我不知道。他们只是把她放进了。

source: We don’t know. So let’s just be careful. Especially around her... new friend.
target: 我们不知道。所以就小心点。特别是在她……新朋友身边。

source: Shhh. I think they might be listening.
target: 嘘，我觉得他们可能在监听。

source: So sore… Haven’t been able to move for hours.
target: 好痛……好几个小时无法动弹。

source: Which’ll kill us first you think? The Doctor, or hunger?
target: 你觉得哪个会先要了我们的命?是博士，还是饥饿?

source: When’s the last time you ate?
target: 你最后一次吃东西是什么时候?

source: Neither can I… But it feels like forever.
target: 我也不……但感觉就像永远一样。

source: I prefer not to even think about it.
He's stretchy, he's gummy, he's squishy, he's funny-
target: 他能伸能屈，像口香糖，软绵绵，还很有趣-

source: He's silly, he's gooey, he's sticky, he's gluey-
target: 他很傻，他黏糊糊，他粘黏黏

source: So many toys in one!
target: 这么多玩具合为一体!

source: Triple kind of friend and triple type of fun!
target: 三种类型的朋友，三种乐趣!

source: Fun until the day that you die!
target: 直到你死去的那一天都充满乐趣!

source: Call the number on screen, and order your Doey today.
target: 拨打屏幕上的号码，今天就订购你的多伊。

source: Order now while supplies last-- shipping and handling-- costs may vary--
target: 数量有限，立即订购-- 如包含运费和手续费-- 费用可能会有变化--

source: This one! This one! I wanna open this one!
I knew it! This is the one I wanted!
target: 我就知道!这就是我想要的那个!

source: There's a card too, dear! Open the card!
target: 这里还有一张卡片，亲爱的!打开卡片看看!

source: We're going to the Playtime Factory?!
target: 我们要去玩具工厂了吗?

source: (Sighs) He's not listening to a thing I say, is he?
target: (叹气)他根本没在听我说话，是吧?

source: Grab him! Grab him! Somebody grab him!
target: 抓住他!抓住他!来个人抓住他!

source: Shut down the machines! Everyone shut down the machines!
target: 关掉那些机器!大家快把机器都关掉!

source: And somebody shut off that cam--
target: 还有人把那摄像机关掉--

source: Your suggestions have failed to produce the results I’m after.
target: 你的建议未能产生我想要的结果。

source: Have I made an error in allowing your survival?
target: 允许你存活下来是不是我的一个错误?

source: Of course not. We just need more time to perfect the-
target: 当然不是。我们只需要更多时间来完善-

source: Time is precisely what we do not have.
target: 时间正是我们所没有的。

source: Then I suggest you find some more.
That, or give me labs access. At least with the two of us-
target: 要么这样，要么给我实验室的权限。至少我们两人一起-

source: That is out of the question. You will stay put.
target: 这完全不可能。你必须待在原地。

source: Fine, but you have no staff, virtually no test subjects; It’s hardly ideal conditions.
target: 好吧，但你没有员工，几乎没有任何试验对象； 这可不是理想的条件。

source: Even when this place was fully operational, we were beating our heads against this.
target: 即使这个地方全面运作时，我们还是为此绞尽脑汁。

source: You can’t expect to do it on your own so quickly.
target: 你不能期望这么快独自完成这一切。

source: The situation necessitates it be done quickly.
target: 形势要求我们必须尽快完成。

source: I’m just giving you the facts, and the fact is we need more time or this isn’t going to work.
target: 我只是给你事实，事实是我们需要更多时间，否则这就行不通。

source: I can only be reactive up here.
target: 在这上面我只能被动应对。

source: Then of what use are you?
You know I’m still your best shot at cracking that secret.
target: 你知道我还是破解那个秘密的最佳人选。

source: If I weren’t, you would have already killed me.
target: 如果不是这样，你早就杀了我。

source: A sound observation. Yes, You have made yourself useful.
target: 很敏锐的观察。是的，你让自己变得很有用了。

source: Provide me more options, I will try again.
target: 给我更多选择，我会再试一次。

source: But… if you are stalling, or worse…
target: 但是… 如果你在拖延，或者更糟…

source: Remember, your usefulness is the only reason you were not stripped for meat and spare parts.
target: 记住，你的利用价值是你没被拆解成肉和备用零件的唯一原因。

source: It looks like he’s waking up.
Oh no... They didn’t. Those backstabbing traitors.
target: 哦不... 他们不是吧。那些背信弃义的叛徒。

source: Dr. Sawyer? Can you hear me?
target: 索耶博士?你能听见我吗?

source: Who else is in there with you? You enjoying watching me writhe like one of them?
target: 还有谁在那儿和你一起?你是不是在看我像他们一样扭动很开心?

source: (Pained groans) My head, feels like it’s splitting in two.
target: (痛苦的呻吟) 我的头，感觉像是要裂成两半。

source: This is wrong, you must have done something wrong.
target: 这不对劲，你一定做了什么坏事。

source: Some disorientation is to be expected, it’ll-
target: 有一些迷失方向感是可以预料的，这会-

source: You spineless cowards, after all I’ve done for this project, for this company…
target: 你们这些软骨头的懦夫，我为这个项目，为这家公司做了这么多…

source: Leith Pierre, of course it’d be you.
You have no idea what kind of mistake you’ve just made.
target: 你完全不知道你刚刚犯了多大的错误。

source: Really? From where I’m sitting, you’re the one who keeps making mistakes that need fixing.
target: 真的?从我坐的地方看，你才是那个不断犯错需要修正的人。

source: We gave you so many opportunities to clean up your own messes, but you just couldn’t do it, could you?
target: 我们给了你那么多机会去收拾你的烂摊子，但你就是做不到，不是吗?

source: What? You think you can do better?
target: 什么?你以为你能做得更好?

source: Nobody else can do what I do! You need my knowledge- my intellect!
target: 没人能替代我!你需要我的知识-我的智慧!

source: Why do you think you’re sitting in there right now, and not in Boxy’s stomach?
target: 你为什么认为你现在坐在那儿，而不是在Boxy的肚子里?

source: Let me tell you how this is gonna go, Sawyer.
target: 让我告诉你事情会怎么发展，索耶。

source: From now on, you’re here to give the lab boys answers when they need them, and carry out procedures when and how we tell you to. That’s it.
target: 从现在开始，你就在这里，当实验室人员需要答案时就给他们答案，并在我们告诉你的时间和方式下执行程序。仅此而已。

source: You’ll be like an open book to us whenever we want.
target: 我们想让你什么时候像一本打开的书一样对我们都行。

source: So fight, or give in, or whatever, because either way we own the infrastructure you’re wired into.
target: 所以是战斗，或者屈服，或者随便怎样，因为不管怎么样我们都拥有你所连接的基础设施。

source: When I get my hands on you, you’re a dead man!
This temper is a bad look for you, Harley.
target: 哈雷，这种脾气对你可不好看。

source: After a brief…interruption, we’ve successfully extracted Subject 1322.
target: 经过短暂的...中断，我们成功提取了1322号样本。

source: Specifically, 1322B, from the Home Sweet Home.
target: 特别是1322B，来自于甜蜜之家。

source: Before said interruption, I attempted to detail the subject’s condition.
target: 在所述中断发生前，我试图详细记录受试者的状态。

source: And overview the suitability of one “Kevin Barnes” in relation to “Project: Doey”.
target: 以及一个「凯文·巴恩斯」对于「项目:多伊」的适应性概览。

source: The “neural abnormalities” noted in Dr. Newman’s report are detailed in connection to behavioral issues demonstrated within Playcare.
target: 纽曼博士报告中提到的「神经异常」与在Playcare中表现出的行为问题有关。

source: Trouble getting along with others, aggressive and often confrontational social tendencies,
target: 难以与他人相处，行为具有侵略性且常表现为对抗性的社交倾向，

source: and an otherwise combative nature clearly relay that Kevin is, put simply, a problem child.
target: 以及那种随时可能爆发的争斗本性，简单来说，凯文正是一个问题儿童。

source: What friends he DOES have, he’s reported to have attacked in moments of… intense play.
target: 就连他有的那么几个朋友，他也曾在「激烈的玩耍」中攻击过他们。

source: The subject excels in all physical tests. Reflexes, reaction time, and mental fortitude all tested well above average in Game Station examinations.
target: 该实验对象在所有体能测试中表现出色。反射、反应时间和心理韧性在游戏站的测试中均远超平均水平。

source: So, in spite of said concerns, in Dr. Sawyer’s eyes, Kevin is ideal for the Project.
target: 因此，尽管有这些顾虑，在索耶博士眼中，凯文是项目理想的对象。

source: However, if his use in this particular experiment is to move forward, we need to ensure we’re not creating a time bomb just as we’ve begun stabilizing the entire Project.
target: 然而，如果他在这一特定实验中的使用要继续下去，我们需要确保我们在整个项目刚开始稳定时不是在制造定时炸弹。

source: If we’re to create an experiment that can fulfill multiple assigned roles, we can’t allow any single consciousness to throw the others off…
target: 如果我们想创造一个可以完成多个分配角色的实验，我们不能允许任何一个意识干扰到其他的…

source: Even a simple misregulation of emotions means we have nine-hundred pounds of dough that can shift however it pleases,
target: 即使是简单的情绪误调，也意味着我们有九百磅面团可以随意变化。

source: and can turn on even those it trusts, simply because it was overwhelmed by a stray feeling…
target: 并能对它信任的人翻脸无情，仅仅因为它被一种突如其来的情绪淹没…

source: Regardless, Sawyer’s word is law, and Subjects 1322A and C are to be gathered for processing first thing tomorrow morning…
target: 不管怎样，索耶博士的话就是法律，1322A和C样本明天早上第一件事就是被收集处理…

source: Thus, all we can do is plan our safeguards accordingly…
target: 因此，我们所能做的就是相应地计划好我们的安全保障措施…

source: Yes, that’s ALL we can do…
target: 是的，那已经是我们能做的全部了…

source: Sir, ma’am, I ask that you remain calm whenever you interact with the… patient.
target: 先生，女士，我要求你们在与……患者互动时保持冷静。

source: He’s only been awake a few days now.
In many respects, he’s still adjusting.
target: 在许多方面，他仍在适应。

source: Is that… Is that him? Is that my boy?
target: 那是… 那是他吗?那是我的孩子吗?
哦，乔治。那是我们的儿子。

source: Why does he look like that?
What did you do to him!?
That’s our son in there. Our SON.
target: 那是我们的儿子。我们的儿子。

source: Dear, look at it. That’s not even human!
target: 亲爱的，看看它。那甚至不是个人!

source: Let’s just talk to him. Y-You’ll see. Let’s just go in there and talk to him.
target: 我们只需要跟他谈谈。你……你看了就知道。我们就进去和他谈谈。

source: Can we? Can we talk to him?
target: 我们能吗?我们能和他说话吗?

source: Go on in, whenever you’re ready.
target: 随时进去吧，准备好了就行。

source: Jack, I… I want you to know… I’m so, SO sorry.
target: 杰克，我……我想让你知道……我非常，非常抱歉。

source: I’ve never forgiven myself for what happened.
target: 我从未原谅过自己所发生的一切。

source: I’ve played it all back a million times in my head, and I know, I KNOW there had to be… SOMETHING I could have done.
target: 我已经在脑海中回放了一百万次，我清楚地知道，我本该做些什么的。

source: I could’ve reached just a little further. I could’ve noticed a little sooner. I could’ve–…
target: 我本可以把手伸得再远一点。我本可以再早一点注意到。我本可以–…

source: But we have you back now. That’s what’s important.
target: 但我们已经把你带回来。这才是最重要的。

source: J-Jack?... Honey, it’s me. It’s mommy.
target: 杰... 杰克?亲爱的，是我。是妈妈呀。

source: Yes. Yes! It’s mommy and daddy. You remember, don’t you?
target: 是的，是的!是妈妈和爸爸。你记得，对吧?

source: Hey. Hey, you’ll be okay, I promise. Mommy’s only here to talk.
target: 嘿。嘿，你会没事的，我保证。妈妈只是来和你谈谈。

source: No, no I don’t WANT to talk. Get out!!
Susan, I think we should leave…
target: 苏珊，我觉得我们应该离开……

source: I’m not leaving you. Not ever again, do you hear me?
target: 我不会离开你。再也不会让你离开，你听到了吗?

source: Susan, Susan get away from it!
Mommy won’t lie to you, Jackie. Mommy won’t hurt you.
target: 妈妈不会骗你，杰克。妈妈不会伤害你。
求你了！打开这扇门！求你！
(吹口哨)真是一条很长的路啊。

source: So, this is what we have to work with?
target: 所以，这就是我们必须处理的情况?

source: Good. Remember, our timetable here is tight.
target: 很好。记住，我们的时间表很紧。

source: If there’s anything you need from me, do not hesitate to—
target: 如果你需要我做任何事，请尽管开口——

source: Actually… I’ve got something I want to talk to you about.
target: 实际上……我有些事想和你谈谈。

source: My company, we’ve built a lot for you over the years, and believe me, we’ve always been accomodating.
target: 我们公司多年来为你建造了很多东西，相信我，我们一向都很配合。

source: We just did the work you paid us to do…
target: 我们只是完成了你花钱让我们做的事……

source: I don’t like what I’m supposed to be building here.
target: 我不喜欢我在这里要建造的东西。

source: Look, the Game Station? Whatever. It’ll be fun for the kids.
target: 你看，游戏站?随便吧。它会让孩子玩得很开心。

source: Undergound production plants? Sure. Maximize production. Makes a kind of sense. As much as any of this, I suppose…
target: 地下生产工厂?当然。最大化生产。有一定的道理。我想，就像这里面的其他东西一样……

source: What in the world would a toy company need with a prison?
target: 一家玩具公司要监狱干什么?

source: When my people were building Playcare, all Mr. Ludwig could talk about was how much good it could do.
target: 当我的人建造Playcare时，路德维希先生说的就只有它能带来多少好处。

source: And all you needed was a look at the man to know he believed every word of it…
target: 而且只需要看看这个人，就知道他相信自己的每一句话……

source: I need to hear that this is still the same company.
target: 我需要听到这仍然是同一家公司。

source: If we’re going to make this thing for you, then I need that assurance.
target: 如果我们打算为你做这个东西，我需要你的保证。

source: It’s a game. Something for the kids.
target: 是个游戏。给孩子们玩的东西。

source: Let me give you a bit of history, friend.
target: 让我给你一点历史背景，朋友。

source: In 1972, you signed a contract. A legally binding piece of paper that says whatever is asked of you, you do it.
target: 1972年，你签署了一份合同。一份具有法律效力的文件，上面写着，无论对你提出什么要求，你都要照做。

source: In 1990, you signed another. A renewal.
target: 1990年，你又签署了一份。一份续约合同。

source: In it, had you bothered at all to read it, you’d have found a small clause.
target: 如果你稍微花点时间读一下，就会发现里面有一小段条款。

source: “Any and all directives will be accomplished in the appropriate time, and with appropriate compensation should the project be completed to satisfaction.”
target: 「任何及所有指令都将在适当的时间内完成，如果项目按要求完成，将给予适当的补偿。」

source: Your name rests at the bottom of that document, and I remember because it was the ugliest bit of cursive I’ve ever seen.
target: 你的名字就在那份合同的底部，我还记得，因为那是我见过最丑的草书体。

source: So now you do the work, because we’ve given you a directive.
target: 那么现在你来完成工作，因为我们已经给了你指示。
R-里特曼先生，我们已经靠近——
是的。是的，我们正是如此。

source: Great things that will someday make a lot of people very happy.
target: 让许多人有一天会感到非常幸福的伟大事情。

source: But to do so, to make that dream real, we need this.
target: 但是，要做到这一点，让那个梦想成真，我们必须拥有这个。

source: Otherwise, there’s a place we’ll all fall.
target: 否则，我们会全都掉进某个地方。

source: I’m a businessman, Mr. Silva. And I don’t like to get angry.
target: 我是商人，席尔瓦先生。我不喜欢发火。

source: I get paid to see that things get done.
target: 我的任务就是确保事情完成。

source: And this, like everything else, will get done.
target: 而这一点，和其他一切一样，都会完成。

source: [Press the Hand Trigger to launch built-in flares.]
target: [按下扳机以发射内置照明弹。]

source: [In dark areas, use flares to light your path forward.]
target: [在黑暗区域，使用照明弹照亮你前进的道路。]

source: [Rope, oil, and other resources can be burnt on contact.]
target: [绳索、油等资源接触后可被点燃。]

source: [... And the results can be deadly.]

target: [别伤到自己，也别伤到其他员工。]

source: It was awful. So so awful…
target: 真是太可怕了，太可怕了…

source: I didn’t want… This w-wasn’t what I…
I thought we were gonna leave. Leave the factory. Not this…
target: 我以为我们会离开，要离开这座工厂。而不是这样…

source: Prototype says we can’t leave. Not now. Not ever…
target: 原型说我们无法离开。现在不能离开，以后也不能离开…

source: I hate him. I hate him, and I hate this place, and I hate that he’s…
target: 我恨他。我恨他，我恨这个地方，我恨他变得…

source: He explained everything, and he’s right.
target: 他解释了一切，他说得对。

source: We can’t leave. It’s too risky. What they did to us...
target: 我们无法离开。风险太大了。他们对我们所做的那些事...

source: We can’t ever let it happen to us or anyone ever again.
target: 我们绝不能让这种事发生在我们或任何人身上。

source: Doesn’t make me feel better about the bodies, though. What he was saying about them.
target: 不过，关于那些尸体，我仍旧无法释怀。他说了些什么关于他们的事。

source: I know there’s not really another option. The toys’ will starve otherwise, they’ll die…
target: 我知道确实没有其他选择。否则玩具将会饿死，他们会死去…

source: I wish you were here, Dad.
I could really use one of your talks right about now. You’d know what to say.
target: 我现在真的很需要你的一场谈话。你知道该怎么说。

source: When you were running this place, you always knew what to say…
target: 你经营这个地方时，你总是知道该说什么…

source: Hi. My name is Leith Pierre, and I’m the Head of Innovation here at Playtime Co.
target: 嗨，我叫雷思·皮埃尔，我是游戏时间公司的创新主管。

source: If you’re seeing this, you must be very, very lost.
target: 如果你看到了这个，你一定迷路了，非常非常迷路。

source: Well, rest assured friend, our state-of-the-art laboratory is just up ahead.
target: 好吧，放心吧朋友，我们最先进的实验室就在前方。

source: Why dontcha just go on inside and tap one of our scientists on the shoulder.
target: 为什么你不去里面拍拍我们某位科学家的肩膀呢。

source: Tell ‘em you're lost, they'll be glad to help.
target: 告诉他们你迷路了，他们会很乐意帮助你。

source: Let’s be honest. You're not supposed to be here.
target: 说实话。你不应该在这里。

source: This is the single most high security, high clearance section of the whole factory.
target: 这是整个工厂中安全级别最高的区域。

source: When somebody finds you down here, you will be shot.
target: 当有人在这下面发现你时，你会被击毙。

source: And before you get any ideas, don’t think you can just sneak away either.
target: 在你产生任何念头之前，别以为你可以偷偷离开。

source: No, the second you put this tape in, it set off an alarm.
target: 你一插入这盘磁带，就触发了警报。

source: So if anyone’s home, they know exactly where you are.
target: 所以如果有人在家，他们就会知道你确切的位置。

source: Pretty nifty, huh? Security is very important to us here.
target: 很巧妙吧?安全对我们这里来说非常重要。

source: If I were you, I’d start running.
target: 如果我是你，我已经开始跑了。

source: When you didn’t answer, I… I mean…
target: 当你没有回应的时候，我……我是说……
我没事。(抽鼻子) 真的。

source: Did the bad men hurt you?
There’s nothing more they can do to hurt me.
target: 已经没有比这更伤我的事了。

source: Nothing more than what they’ve already done.
target: 不会再有比他们已经做过的更严重的了。
波比，有什么事在困扰着你。

source: Something you…. need to talk about?
I don’t need anything tonight. Ollie, I just want to sleep.
target: 我今晚什么都不需要，奥利。我只是想睡觉。

source: I think there’s more to this. More that you’re not telling me.
target: 我觉得这里还有更多问题。更多你没有告诉我的事。

source: I know what you’re doing Poppy. Talking like that. Don’t think for a second that I believe it.
target: 我知道你在做什么，波比。像那样说话。别以为我真的相信。

source: Just tell me what you’re feeling. Please, just talk to me honestly.
target: 告诉我你的感受吧。求你了，跟我说实话。

source: Talk? Talk?! You want me to talk!?
And what will talking do, huh?!
Will talking to you make them stop?!
target: 跟你说话能让他们停下吗?!

source: I’m scared, Ollie. Is that what you want to hear?
target: 我很害怕，奥利。这就是你想听的吗?

source: I’m scared, and I’m angry, and…
target: 我很害怕，也很生气，而且……

source: And I really don’t know what to do…
target: 我真的不知道该怎么办...

source: The bad men don’t say what they want. They don’t listen.
target: 那些坏人不说他们想要什么。他们不听。

source: They don’t care how much anything hurts…
target: 他们才不管事情有多疼……

source: It’s been weeks and weeks of taking things out and putting them back in and taking things out and putting them back in.
target: 已经好多好多周了，他们取出一些东西，再放回去，再取出，再放回去。

source: Nothing’s EVER gotten better. And it’ll never GET better.
target: 从来没有好过。也永远不会变好。

source: But you know what scares me more than anything, Ollie?
target: 但你知道什么比什么都让我害怕，奥利?

source: It scares me that every time they do it...
target: 每次他们这么做时，都让我害怕...

source: Every time they peel me open...
I hate them. And I hate him. And I hate…
target: 我恨他们。我恨他。我也恨...

source: I’m nothing now, Ollie. No one. I’m a thing…
target: 我现在什么都不是了，奥利。没人。我只是个东西……

source: And nothing they can do to me hurts more than that…
target: 他们对我做的任何事都没有比这更痛的了...

source: You’re not nothing to me. You’re Poppy.
target: 你对我来说不是无足轻重的人。你是波比。

source: And talking with you. Like this…
I know it doesn’t make any of what they do right. It can’t…
target: 我知道他们所做的一切都无关对错，它不能...

source: But it makes me feel like a piece of me is still here. No matter how small they try to make it.
target: 但它让我觉得我的一部分仍然存在，不管他们想让它变得多渺小。

source: Next to all that, next to whatever they do… it means everything.
target: 相比那些东西，不管他们做什么……这很重要。

source: I’m here, Poppy. For you, I’ll always be here.
target: 我在这儿呢，波比。为了你，我永远都在。

source: Don’t lurk out there. It’s weird. Just come on in. Being early isn’t a crime.
target: 别在那儿鬼鬼祟祟的。这很奇怪。直接进来吧。早到并不是犯罪。

source: You know why I asked you here, right?
target: 你知道我为什么叫你来这儿吧?

source: (Sighs) Why are we doing this dance again, boss?
target: (叹气) 我们又在这跳这舞了吗，老板?

source: Because you were reported, and all reports for my people come back to me.
target: 因为你被举报了，所有关于我的人报告都会回到我这儿。

source: Look, I’m not here to place blame. Just tell me your side of this.
target: 听着，我不是来指责谁的。告诉我你这边的情况。

source: This guy, Rod, he works the line. One of those twitchy mooks with the side eye.
target: 有个叫罗德的家伙在生产线上工作。他是那种眼睛斜视、颤颤巍巍的小混混。

source: And this guy, Rod, he saw me drop a box he and his boys filled. Kinda irked em’.
target: 那个叫罗德的家伙，看到我把一个他们填满的箱子掉了。他有点生气。

source: I think he was joking, that’s probably how he meant it, but he dropped some line about me “disappearing.”
target: 我想他是在开玩笑，他可能就是这个意思，但他提到一句关于我「消失」的话。

source: Him and the other guys laughed. I was…Having a bad day, so I… I yelled at him a bit. About him. About the company.
target: 他和其他人笑了。我当时心情不好，所以……我朝他喊了几句。关于他，关于公司。

source: And where were you when this happened?
Look, I… I don’t mean to keep causing you trouble, Rich. You’re good to me. To all of us.
target: 听着，我……我不想总给你添麻烦，里奇。你对我们所有人都很好。

source: But the company isn’t good to you. Or to Rod or me. Or to anyone.
target: 但公司对你不好。对罗德不好，对我不好，对任何人都不好。

source: Leith says Playtime is better than ever, but profits aren’t people. And the profit margins betray just how on edge everyone is.
target: 雷思说游戏时间比以往任何时候都好，但利润不是人。利润的边际正显示出每个人是多么的紧张。

source: Hell, anywhere else, I’d have probably LIKED Rod.
target: 见鬼，换个地方，我可能就喜欢上罗德了。

source: But because he said it like that, and with all the rumors… I-I just don’t know if I can take it anymore.
target: 但是他那样说，加上谣言……我真的不知道自己能不能再承受了。

source: And it feels wrong that no one says anything as loud as they should.
target: 那种沉默让我觉得不对。明明人们该大声说出来的事。

source: Look, I get it. This company is far from angelic. Trust me, I know that.
target: 听着，我明白了。这家公司远非天使。相信我，我知道。

source: But there are smarter ways to go about what you did…
target: 但处理你所做的事有更聪明的方式……

source: Hey. No matter what the executives say, no matter the looks you get, just know that I’VE got your back, kid.
target: 嘿。不管那些高管怎么说，不管你得到什么样的目光，只要知道我支持你，孩子。

source: Shipping is a family. We look out for each other. That’s the way it is now.
target: 运输部门是个大家庭。我们互相照应。这就是现在的状况。

source: So don’t fight, don’t shout, just come talk to ME from now on, okay?
target: 所以，别斗了，别喊了，从现在起直接跟我谈谈，行不?

source: I don’t want another report on my desk like this one.
target: 我不希望桌上再出现这样的报告了。

source: I fight for you, ALL of you. And I’m in a position where I can do so.
target: 我为你们所有人战斗。而且我处在一个可以这么做的位置。

source: It’s… It's good to know not EVERYONE here is terrible to us.
target: 知道这里并非人人都对我们不好，这感觉……真好。
不是所有人，孩子。不是所有人。

source: So. Ms. Greyber. Have you considered what we talked about?
target: 那么，格雷伯女士。你考虑过我们讨论的事情了吗?

source: Yes, Mr. Pierre. I… I won’t lie, I was at a loss for words at first.
target: 是的，皮埃尔先生。我…我坦白说刚开始我真的不知道该说什么。

source: The information hit me pretty hard. I felt so badly- I still do- for the ones that go through the, um, testing.
target: 这些信息对我冲击很大。我对那些经历，呃，测试的孩子感到非常难过--现在也是。

source: Yes. It hurts to see them hurt, I don’t think there’s any way around that feeling…
target: 是的。看到他们受伤我也很难过，我觉得这种感觉无论如何都避免不了…

source: I did some soul searching, and got to thinking about the bigger picture…
target: 我进行了深入反思，开始思考更大的局面…
关于你的研究员们写的内容。

source: Well, the work itself, what you’ve all been able to do… I mean, it’s nothing short of a miracle.
target: 嗯，你们所做的工作，你们所有人能做到的事…简直就是一个奇迹。

source: I know you have more goals to hit, but even as is, just, wow.
target: 我知道你还有更多目标要达成，但即便是现在这样，也已经非常惊艳了。

source: Do they know when it’ll be… fully ready?
target: 他们知道什么时候会…完全准备好吗?

source: We’re still working out the timeline.
You know, the project lead- Dr. Sawyer- wasn’t sure about giving you that information in the first place. He thinks your affection towards those kids could be a liability…
target: 说起来，项目负责人——索耶博士——当初还不确定要不要给你那些信息。他认为你对那些孩子的爱好可能会是个负担…

source: What do you think about that?
I took this job because I wanted to help change kids’ lives for the better.
target: 我接受了这份工作，因为我想要帮助改变更多孩子的生活，让它变得更好。

source: Of course these procedures are far from ideal; I cried like a baby when I read them.
target: 当然这些流程远非理想；我读它们的时候哭得像个孩子。

source: But I started looking past the here and now, started looking down the road a bit. That’s when it clicked.
target: 但我开始看穿眼前的一切，开始展望未来。然后就明白了。

source: What your researchers can do down here will someday help a lot of people out there, including so so many kids.
target: 你研究员们在这里所能做到的事未来将会帮助到外面很多人，包括好多好多的孩子。

source: That’s a bigger and better change than I could ever have hoped to make. That’s a change I want to help make.
target: 这是一个比我所能期望做出的更大、更好的改变。这是我想要帮忙实现的改变。

source: Jeez… Hard to imagine how the company will tuck all this under the rug.
target: 天哪……真难以想象公司会怎么把这些都掩盖过去。

source: Where’s that Investigator? Campbell, Lockehart– whatever his name is.
target: 那个调查员呢?坎贝尔，洛克哈特——管他叫什么名字。
在某个地方瞎转悠。不知道。

source: You ask me, the culprit’s obvious. Just needs to be spelled out plain and clear for the bigwigs.
target: 你要问我，罪魁祸首很明显。只需要给大人物们清清楚楚地摆出来。

source: Yeah. Rotten eggs come from rotten chickens, ya know?
target: 是啊。要知道，坏鸡蛋总是坏鸡下的，对吧?

source: Can’t get more rotten a chicken than him.
target: 比他更烂的家伙可不多了。

source: I don’t know, just seems too careless that a guy so smart wouldn’t cover his ass.
target: 我不知道，只是觉得一个这么聪明的人居然不掩盖自己的痕迹，未免太不小心了。

source: I mean, if the investigator finds evidence of this being his fault…
target: 我是说，要是调查员找到这是他责任的证据……
(轻声笑)希望布克瑟还是那么饿。

source: Right, and are we just stuffing the experiments back where they came from?
target: 是啊，我们难道就是把实验品塞回它们来的地方?

source: Acting like all this didn’t happen?
target: 然后装作这一切都没有发生过?

source: Because I guarantee it won’t be so easy to toss a new coat of paint over sixty visitors dead.
target: 因为我保证，要掩盖六十名访客的死亡可不是刷层新漆那么容易。

source: Or the dozen Resource Extraction Specialists we’ve got swimming in the bellies of those things.
target: 还有那些游荡在怪兽肚子里的一打资源采集专家们。

source: I’m sure that’s taken care of already…
target: 我相信那已经处理好了……

source: But I hear there’s plans. Something big. Somewhere to put them.
target: 不过我听说有计划了。一个大计划。找个地方安置他们。

source: With any luck, that means stuff like this, and people like him, will be a thing of the past.
target: 要是运气好，这事儿，还有像他这样的人，将会成为历史。
这种鲁莽的行为必须停止。

source: The Doctor has no regard for the safety of this facility, or its staff.
target: 博士完全不顾及这个设施及其员工的安全。

source: Or the children in Playcare. I’ve tried to set boundaries with him. He doesn’t listen to me.
target: 还有Playcare里的那些孩子们。我试过给他设定界限。他不听我的。

source: He doesn’t listen to any of us. Not really. Not anymore. And he’s behind schedule.
target: 他不再听我们任何人的。真的。他进度落后了。

source: Playtime may have turned a corner financially, but that doesn’t change the fact that his “Bigger Bodies Initiative” is still a money hole.
target: 游戏时间可能在财务上有了转机，但这并不改变他的「更大身躯计划」仍然是个烧钱的无底洞。

source: And how do you suggest we do that?
This wouldn’t be the first time we’ve made someone disappear.
target: 这又不是我们第一次让人消失了。
我们不能杀了他, 艾迪。

source: Because like it or not, we need him.
target: 因为不管喜欢与否，我们需要他。

source: Eddie’s right though, Sawyer can’t keep leading this project.
target: 埃迪说得对，索耶不能继续领导这个项目了。

source: (Chuckles) So we just ask him to step down? Take a demotion?
target: (轻笑)所以我们只是让他辞职?降职?

source: I’m not disagreeing. Huggy loose in the woods, that business with CatNap, the whole Stoll thing-
target: 我没意见。哈吉在树林里乱跑，瞌睡猫的事情，整个Stoll的事件——

source: And half a dozen other incidents-
Right, and all of that pales in comparison to the Theater Incident.
target: 对，所有这些都比不上剧场事件。

source: (Shudders) I don’t even want to talk about that…
So… we can’t kill the sonofabitch, but we need to knock him out of the equation.
target: 所以...我们不能杀了这个混蛋，但我们需要让他离开这个方程式。

source: There is one thing I can think of…
Hey, watch the door! Watch the door!
There you go, bud. You’re okay.
“Okay”? Look at me, I’m a mess!
We were trying to bring supplies back up to the elevator, but we got jumped.
target: 我们正试图把补给运回电梯，但遭到伏击。

source: Had to turn all the way back around.
target: 不得不一路折返回来了。

source: They took everything we had! Right after one of em bit my leg!
target: 他们抢走了我们所有的东西!就在其中一个咬了我的腿之后!

source: Keep bite clean. Could get infected otherwise.
target: 保持伤口清洁。否则会感染。

source: So, um… What do we do now?
target: 所以，嗯...我们现在要做什么?

source: For starters, you two stay here tonight. Let things settle down outside. I’ll find more food for you to bring up to Playcare.
target: 首先，你们俩今晚待在这里。让外面的事情平息下来。我会去找更多食物带回Playcare。

source: Sorry we lost the supplies. It won’t happen again.
target: 很抱歉我们丢了补给。不会再发生了。

source: The important thing is you’re both okay… aside from that bite, that is.
target: 最重要的是你们俩都没事...除了那个咬伤。

source: Hey, doc, let me grab some wound cream for our pal here.
target: 嘿，博士，让我给我们的朋友拿些创伤膏。

source: I uh… I’m not sure if this thingy is on. But I need to talk. And…
target: 呃……我不确定这玩意儿是否开着，但我需要说话。而且……

source: I can’t talk about this with anyone else...
target: 我不能和别人谈论这件事……

source: For the past few months, the fighting’s been bad… Real bad…
target: 在过去的几个月里，战斗很激烈……非常激烈……

source: I’ve uh… seen a lot of stuff I probably shouldn’t.
target: 呃……我看到了许多我本不该看到的东西。

source: It’s been hard to… Keep my head straight.
The others, they look to me to know what to do. To know where to go…
target: 其他人，他们都看着我，想知道该做什么，该去哪里……

source: For a long while, we had Poppy to tell us.
target: 很长一段时间，我们有波比告诉我们。

source: Go here. Go there. Do this. And it all made sense too. Poppy was nice…
target: 去这里，去那里，做这个。一切都很合理，波比人很好……

source: I don’t know what happened, or where she went… But it’s scary here without her.
target: 我不知道发生了什么，也不知道她去了哪里……但没有她这里很可怕。

source: Maybe she ran… Just like I have...
target: 也许她逃了……就像我一样……

source: I’m here, outside the Prison, in front of…
target: 我现在在监狱外面，面前是……

source: I’d almost forgotten it was all here…
target: 我几乎忘记了所有的一切……

source: And seeing this again, it’s given me reason to think…
target: 再次看到这一切，给了我思考的理由……

source: I could make for the exit. It’s all I’d wanted for the longest time.
target: 我可以冲向出口。这是我一直以来的唯一愿望。

source: But there are others inside. Others… that aren’t like me.
target: 但里面还有其他人。其他人……和我不一样。

source: They’re hungry and scared like I am, but they’re not me. They can’t go where I can.
target: 他们像我一样饥饿和害怕，但他们不是我。他们不能去我能去的地方。

source: But… they mean a lot to me, a lot more than I thought they did.
target: 但……他们对我意义重大，远超我想象。

source: And having seen what I have, knowing how they see me. How much they need me…
target: 在目睹了我所看到的一切，知道他们如何看待我，我是多么被需要……

source: I wanted to make this in case I ever doubt or forget that.
target: 我希望在我怀疑或忘记之前录下这些。

source: Yeah… Yeah, that’s all. See ya.
target: 是啊… 是啊，就这些。回头见。

source: Two o’clock, huh? Best time of the day.
target: 两点钟，对吧?一天中最棒的时间。

source: So, uh, what block are you again?.
target: 所以，呃，你到底在哪一区?

source: Can’t say I hear much about that one.
target: 我可没怎么听说过那里。

source: Know what we get in the East?
target: 你知道我们在东区有什么吗?

source: Toys banging on the walls, crying for their parents, their Counselors, whatever.
target: 玩具砸在墙上，哭着找父母、找辅导员，随便什么。

source: It goes ALL day and night… And it just wears on ya, ya know?
target: 他们整天整夜地吵… 真的让人受不了，你知道吗?

source: I’d KILL for a little security. And quiet.
target: 我愿意付出一切来换取一点点安全保障和安静。

source: Know what we get in the North?
target: 你知道我们在北区有什么吗?

source: Whatever they are, they aren’t people anymore. Their cells might as well be cages.
target: 无论他们是什么，他们都不再是人了。他们的牢房其实就跟笼子一样。

source: They’re animals. Sick. Twisted. Just instincts and anger.
target: 他们就是动物。病态、扭曲。只剩下本能和愤怒。

source: That’s all that’s left of them.
target: 那已经是他们的全部了。

source: Sure, but at least then it’s not like yelling at your own kids for them to be quiet though, ya know?
target: 当然，但至少那样你就不用冲着你自己的孩子喊让他们安静，对吧?

source: I mean, if you had to listen to them—
target: 我是说，如果你不得不听他们的话——

source: (Exhales) So much for our two o’clock.
Yeah, we really do have it rough, don’t we?
target: 是啊，我们的日子可真是不好过，对吧?

source: (Terrified) Oh god, no no no no no.
Doctor! Doctor, what’s going on?! What’s happening, it’s–
target: 博士!博士，发生什么事了?!这是怎么回事，是——

source: Yes. Yes, I can hear it.

target: 他们发动了一场相当壮观的叛乱。(轻笑）

source: How could this happen? There’s failsafes. Security measures. They…
target: 这怎么可能呢?有应急措施、安防手段，它们…

source: Personal agendas have long been the downfall of this company.
target: 个人私欲长久以来一直是这家公司垮台的原因。

source: Is it unreasonable to believe there were conspirators?
target: 认为有同谋者存在，这难道不合理吗?

source: Playtime is filled with vipers and backstabbers.
target: 游戏时间充满了毒蛇与背后捅刀的人。

source: But…But without executive access… How could anyone even get through?
target: 但是… 如果没有执行权限… 怎么会有人进得来?

source: Leith. Stella. Eddie. Only the four of us have that kind of clearance.
target: 雷思、斯特拉、艾迪。只有我们四个人有这种权限。

source: Does any of that matter now? It’s your life you have to protect.
target: 那些现在还有什么重要的?你得保护好自己的命。

source: For all the good it does me! Opening a door at a time won’t get me to the exit, not with those THINGS everywhere.
target: 这些对我有什么好处!一次开一扇门可没法让我逃出去，尤其是到处都是那些东西。

source: You didn’t see what I saw. You didn’t see the trail of limbs down the hall, didn’t hear the things eating. The…
target: 你没看到我看到的东西。你没看到走廊上的肢体碎块，没听到那些东西在进食的声音。那……

source: The wet crunches of bones… God, I…
target: 骨头湿漉漉的断裂声……天哪，我……

source: There is something you can do, Warden. I can help you.
target: 你能做点什么，典狱长。我可以帮助你。

source: How? You’re stuck in there. You can’t–
target: 怎么出去?你都被困在那里了。你不能——

source: The Omni-Hand. If you give it to me, I can get you anywhere. I’ll have control over everything.
target: 全能之手。如果你把它给我，我可以带你去任何地方。我将掌控一切。

source: I can shut some doors, open others. I can make you a pathway that leads right to the exit.
target: 我可以关上一些门，再打开另一些。我可以为你创造一条直达出口的路径。

source: If you want to wait to get torn to pieces, that’s your prerogative, but look at your immediate options, Warden.
target: 如果你想等被撕成碎片，那是你的选择，但看看你眼前的选择吧，典狱长。

source: What choice other than this gets you out of here alive?
target: 除了这个，还有什么选择能让你活着离开这里?

source: I’m giving you the tool. Just get me out of here. Please.
target: 我给了你工具。只要把我弄出去，求你了。

source: You’ve made a smart decision, Warden.
target: 你做出了一个明智的决定，典狱长。

source: I promise I’ll get you out of here safe and sound.
target: 我保证会把你安全无恙地送出去。

source: Cognitive functionality appears minimal at best.
target: 认知功能看起来极为有限。

source: Send em' up to the Secondary Lab. Maybe they can scrounge up something.
target: 把它们送到二号实验室，也许他们能找到点什么。

source: But this is Playcare, your new home.
target: 但这里是儿童照管中心，你的新家。

source: We're here for you, Timmy. We always will be.
target: 我们在这里陪着你，蒂米。我们一直都在。
对象看来稳定。手术成功。

source: Not… getting much response here. Hold.
Can only be changed by the primary player.
You heard her. Now let's get to it.
target: 你听见她说的了。现在开始行动吧。

source: Whenever you’re ready, flip the breaker switch. But be aware, while it’s down, so are Safe Haven’s defenses.
target: 当你准备好了，把断路器关掉。但需要注意，断路器一旦关闭，安全避难所的防御也会关闭。

source: Meaning whatever’s out there has NOTHING keeping it there.
target: 也就是说，不管外面有什么，都没有东西能阻止它。

source: Grab an external resistor. Attach that to the capacitor bank.
target: 拿个外接电阻器，把它接到电容器组上。

source: Good. Now, use the Omni-Hand to override the generator’s chipset protocols so we can yank out the busted surge protector.
target: 好。现在，用全能手来覆盖发电机的芯片组协议，这样我们就能把损坏的浪涌保护器扯出来。

source: Nice. Now put in a new one.
target: 不错。现在放一个新的进去。

source: It’s done… We did it… Good…
target: 完成了……我们做到了……很好……

source: Adjusts the volume of ambient sounds.
Adjust the quality of the anti-aliasing.
Set the language for all of the in-game audio.
target: 设置所有游戏中音频的语言。

source: Select whether to enable the bloom effect.
target: 选择是否启用光晕效果。

source: Adjust the gamma of the in-game image.
target: 调整游戏中图像的伽马值。

source: Button icons will be changed to the following icon type:
target: 按钮图标将更改为以下图标类型:

source: Adjust the camera sensitivity when looking around
target: 调整环顾四周时的摄像机灵敏度。

source: Select whether to enable the camera shake effect.
target: 选择是否启用相机抖动效果。

source: Adjust the contrast of the in-game image.
target: 调整游戏中图像的对比度。

source: Adjusts the volume of dialogue and other vocalizations.
target: 调整对话和其他发声内容的音量。

source: Select whether to enable the film grain effect.
target: 选择是否启用胶片颗粒效果。

source: Adjust the height and width of the in-game view.
target: 调整游戏内视图的高度和宽度。

source: Frame rate limit sets the highest frame rate that is allowed. Set this lower for a more consistent frame rate or higher for the best experience on faster machines. You may need to disable Vsync to reach high frame rates.
target: 帧率限制设置允许的最高帧率。将其设置得较低可获得更稳定的帧率，或在快速机器上设置得较高以获得最佳体验。您可能需要禁用垂直同步以达到高帧率。

source: Frame rate limit when in the menu. Set this lower for a more consistent frame rate or higher for the best experience on faster machines. You may need to disable Vsync to reach high frame rates.
target: 在菜单中运行时的帧率限制。将其设置得较低可获得更稳定的帧率，或在快速机器上设置得较高以获得最佳体验。您可能需要禁用垂直同步以达到高帧率。

source: Frame rate limit when running on battery. Set this lower for a more consistent frame rate or higher for the best experience on faster machines. You may need to disable Vsync to reach high frame rates.
target: 在电池模式下运行时的帧率限制。将其设置得较低以获得更稳定的帧率，或在快速机器上设置得较高以获得最佳体验。您可能需要禁用垂直同步以达到高帧率。

source: Frame rate limit when in the background. Set this lower for a more consistent frame rate or higher for the best experience on faster machines. You may need to disable Vsync to reach high frame rates.
target: 在后台运行时的帧率限制。将其设置得较低可获得更稳定的帧率，或在快速机器上设置得较高以获得最佳体验。您可能需要禁用垂直同步以达到高帧率。

source: This feature only works if 'Window Mode' is set to 'Fullscreen'.
target: 此功能仅在「窗口模式」设置为「全屏」时有效。

source: Set the language for all of the in-game text.
target: 设置所有游戏中文字的语言。

source: Global Illumination controls the quality of dynamically calculated indirect lighting bounces, sky shadowing and Ambient Occlusion. Settings of 'High' and above use more accurate ray tracing methods to solve lighting, but can reduce performance.
target: 全局照明控制动态计算的间接照明反弹、天空阴影和环境光遮挡的质量。'高'及以上设置使用更精确的光线追踪方法来解决光照，但会降低性能。

source:
This key is already assigned to:
Move Back
Assign the key to Jump instead?
target:
此键已经分配给:
向后移动
改为分配到跳跃吗?

source: Lens Flares are the bright streaks of light that appear when looking at a bright light source. Increasing this setting will make lens flares more detailed, but can reduce performance.
target: 镜头光晕是在观看明亮光源时出现的光亮条纹。提高此设置会使光晕更加细致，但可能降低性能。

source: <strong>Note: Changing the framerate setting to {0} or higher might lower your Quality Presets.</>
target: <strong>注意:将帧率设置更改为{0}或更高可能降低你的质量预设。</>

source: Select whether to enable the motion blur effect.
target: 选择是否启用动态模糊效果。

source: <strong>Note: Changing the Quality setting to {0} or higher might limit your framerate.</>
target: <strong>注意:将质量设置更改为{0}或更高可能限制你的帧率。</>

source: Adjust the quality and detail of the post processing effects.
target: 调整后期处理效果的质量和细节。

source: Adjust the resolution at which the in-game scenes are rendered. Lowering this setting reduces the rendered resolution and increases performance.
target: 调整游戏中场景渲染的分辨率。降低此设置可减少渲染分辨率并提升性能。

source: When the Window Mode is set to <strong>Windowed Fullscreen</>, the resolution must match the native desktop resolution.
target: 当窗口模式设置为<strong>窗口化全屏</>时，分辨率必须与本机桌面分辨率一致。

source: Adjusts the saturation of the in-game image.
target: 调整游戏内图像的饱和度。

source: Select whether to run the game in full-screen or windowed mode.
target: 选择游戏是以全屏还是窗口模式运行。

source: Adjust the sharpness level. Increasing this setting will sharpen all on-screen elements.
target: 调整锐化级别。提升此设置将使所有屏幕元素更加清晰。

source: Select whether to show the in-game FPS counter.
target: 选择是否显示游戏中的FPS计数器。

source: Adjusts the volume of sound effects.

target: 调整字幕背景的可见性。

source: Select whether to sync the game's frame rate to the refresh rate of the monitor.
target: 选择是否将游戏帧率同步到显示器的刷新率。

source: Select whether to enable the vignette effect.
target: 选择是否启用暗角效果。

source: Adjust the quality of particle effects.
Your save data is damaged and will not be loaded.
target: 您的存档数据已损坏，将无法加载。

source: Do you think they’ll be nice to me, Dr. White? Whoever adopted me?
target: 你觉得他们会对我好吗，怀特博士?无论是谁收养了我?

source: Yes, I should think so, Danny. I promise you, you’re in good hands.
target: 是的，我想他们会的，丹尼。我向你保证，你得到了很好的照顾。
只有一点点刺痛。就这样。
... 我为什么感觉不到任何东西?

source: Numbness is to be expected, but you'll feel better.
target: 麻木是正常的，但你会感觉好起来的。

source: Don't you worry now, Cassie, the feeling will pass.
target: 别担心，卡西，这种感觉会过去的。

source: Type of waveform to use for oscillation.
If bConstrainAspectRatio is true, black bars will be added if the destination view has a different aspect ratio than this camera requested.
target: 如果 bConstrainAspectRatio 为真，当目标视图的宽高比与此摄像机请求的不同时，将会添加黑边。

source: If true, account for the field of view angle when computing which level of detail to use for meshes.
target: 如果为真，在计算用于网格的不同细节层次时会考虑视角角度。

source: The horizontal field of view (in degrees) in perspective mode (ignored in orthographic mode).
target: 透视模式下的水平视场角(度)(正交模式下忽略)。

source: Off-axis / off-center projection offset as proportion of screen dimensions
target: 屏幕比例的非轴心/非中心投影偏移

source: The far plane distance of the orthographic view (in world units)
target: 正交视图的远平面距离(世界单位)

source: The near plane distance of the orthographic view (in world units)
target: 正交视图的近平面距离(世界单位)

source: The desired width (in world units) of the orthographic view (ignored in Perspective mode)
target: 正交视图所需宽度(世界单位)(透视模式下忽略)

source: The near plane distance of the perspective view (in world units). Set to a negative value to use the default global value of GNearClippingPlane
target: 透视视图的近平面距离(世界单位)。设置为负值时将使用全局默认值 GNearClippingPlane。

source: Indicates if PostProcessSettings should be applied.
Post-process settings to use if PostProcessBlendWeight is non-zero.
target: 如果 PostProcessBlendWeight 为非零时使用的后处理设置。
